1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
TransitOps. Fleet operations, finally under control.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,500
Every day, transport companies lose hours to spreadsheets and phone calls.

3
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:16,000
The same vehicle gets booked twice. A suspended driver ends up on a live route.

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:21,500
Maintenance slips through the cracks. Fuel costs pile up with no clear picture of ROI.

5
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:27,000
Managers guess at utilization. Finance chases receipts. Safety teams react instead of prevent.

6
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:32,500
TransitOps is a transport operations ERP built to replace that fragmentation.

7
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:38,000
One platform for fleet, drivers, dispatches, maintenance, fuel, and financial oversight.

8
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:43,500
Sign in with secure JWT authentication. Each user sees only what their role allows.

9
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:49,000
Admin. Fleet Manager. Safety Officer. Financial Analyst. Driver.

10
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:54,500
Route guards on the frontend. Role checks on every API endpoint on the backend.

11
00:00:54,500 --> 00:01:00,000
Welcome to TransitOps Core — your fleet operations and ROI intelligence control center.

12
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:05,500
Four KPI cards update in real time from server-side aggregations.

13
00:01:05,500 --> 00:01:11,000
Fleet Utilization — what percentage of your active fleet is en route right now.

14
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:16,500
Operational Cost — fuel, maintenance, and approved expenses combined.

15
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:22,000
Estimated Revenue — calculated at two dollars fifty per mile of completed trips.

16
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:27,500
Return on Investment — the efficiency of every asset in your fleet.

17
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:33,000
Below that, live charts: monthly fuel expense trends, maintenance cost by type,

18
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:38,500
and a fleet status pie chart showing Active, On Trip, and In Maintenance allocation.

19
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:44,000
The sidebar shows your three most recent dispatches and compliance alerts from the notification system.

20
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:49,500
In the Vehicles module, register a new asset with plate number, make, model, and payload capacity.

21
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:55,000
Search by plate. Filter by status. Duplicate registrations are blocked at the database level.

22
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:00,500
Inspect any vehicle to view per-asset metrics — fuel cost, maintenance spend, distance driven, and ROI.

23
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:06,000
In the Operator Registry, link a driver to a system user account and record license details.

24
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:11,500
License expiry is validated at dispatch time. Safety scores display on every profile.

25
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:17,000
Now the core workflow — dispatch a trip from the Trips module.

26
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:22,500
Select an Active vehicle. Assign an Active operator. Enter origin, destination, and cargo weight.

27
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:28,000
The UI warns you if cargo exceeds payload. The server enforces it before anything is saved.

28
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:33,500
On successful dispatch, vehicle and driver status automatically transition to On Trip.

29
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:39,000
Complete the trip with an end odometer reading. Both return to Active. Vehicle mileage syncs instantly.

30
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:44,500
Schedule maintenance and the vehicle is removed from dispatch — status moves to In Maintenance.

31
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:50,000
Resolve the work order with cost and mechanic details. The vehicle is available again.

32
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:55,500
Log fuel entries with quantity, cost, and odometer. Record expense claims by category.

33
00:02:55,500 --> 00:03:01,000
Approve pending expenses. Dashboard KPIs refresh automatically — no manual spreadsheet updates.

34
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:06,500
Analytics on the dashboard show fuel trends, maintenance breakdown, and fleet allocation over six months.

35
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:12,000
Per-vehicle metrics deliver fuel efficiency and ROI for individual assets.

36
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:17,500
Now — what happens when someone tries to break the rules?

37
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:23,000
Dispatch a vehicle already on trip — rejected. Assign a suspended driver — blocked.

38
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:28,500
Use a driver with an expired license — stopped. Exceed cargo capacity — denied.

39
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:34,000
Try to dispatch a vehicle in maintenance — the system says no. Every failure returns a clear message.

40
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:39,500
These rules live in the service layer — not in the UI — so they cannot be bypassed.

41
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:45,000
The architecture: React nineteen with Vite and TypeScript on the frontend.

42
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:50,500
Express and MongoDB on the backend. JWT with refresh tokens. Role-based access control.

43
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:56,000
Clean separation — routes, controllers, services, repositories, and Mongoose models.

44
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:01,500
Input validation with express-validator and Zod. TanStack Query for server state. Recharts for analytics.

45
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:07,000
Docker Compose for one-command deployment. Integration tests cover the full dispatch lifecycle.

46
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:12,500
TransitOps replaces spreadsheet chaos with enforced workflows and live financial intelligence.

47
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:18,000
One platform. One source of truth. Built for teams that move the world.

48
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:22,000
Thank you, Odoo Hackathon judges. We are TransitOps.
